The '''National Schools Symphony Orchestra'''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nsso.org/|title=National Schools Symphony Orchestra|accessdate=11 May 2012}}</ref> – known for short as the '''NSSO''' – is a national orchestra in which the members are young people of secondary school age living in and around the [[United Kingdom]].
It was founded in 1995<ref>{{cite news|title=National Schools Symphony Orchestra |url=http://www.malverngazette.co.uk/news/local/9137593.National_Schools_Symphony_Orchestra/ |work=Malvern Gazette |date=14 July 2011 }}</ref> and has several distinguished patrons including [[Patrick Doyle]] and [[John Eliot Gardiner|Sir John Eliot Gardiner]].
